title: Stridbukken Mountain
text: Stridbukken Mountain is a blufflike <a href="mountain">mountain</a> about 1 nautical mile (1.9 km) southwest of <a href="Moteplassen%20Peak">Moteplassen Peak</a>, in the <a href="Borg%20Massif">Borg Massif</a> of <a href="Queen%20Maud%20Land">Queen Maud Land</a>. Mapped by Norwegian cartographers from surveys and air photos by <a href="Norwegian-British-Swedish%20Antarctic%20Expedition">Norwegian-British-Swedish Antarctic Expedition</a> (NBSAE) (1949–52) and named Stridbukken (the hardhead).
